<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Soeer" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Soe'er,</orth> adv. separated from <emph>how, what,</emph> or <emph>who,</emph> with which words it is usually compounded in <emph>howsoe'er</emph> or <emph>howsoever,</emph> etc.: <bibl n="shak. tn 1.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.170" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.112" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 112</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>